caption: Great service every visit. Proper cocktails and the hand pies are delicious.
I must admit, I only came for the art-o-mat they have at their location. Staff was very helpful and nice. Next time I come for the art-o-mat, I'll stay for a drink.

I was on a quest for the perfect hot toddy and I’m happy to say my journey ended here. You can’t go wrong with the drink list here. The cocktails are phenomenal (especially the hot toddy). The service is outstanding, everyone was super friendly and hospitable. I had the Spanish Tortilla for a bite and it was delicious. For a night out with friends or date night I highly recommend this spot.
Yes! Fancy small food. Excellent cocktails.

Love. This. Bar. I don't really live near by but would still call it my go-to neighborhood bar. The staff is so welcoming, the food is solid, and the drinks...the drinks are delicious. They seem to have something new every time I come by. Great wine list, too!  I have to give them props for creating a wonderful experience while still making everyone feel protected and appropriately distanced. It can't be easy right now but they have really gone the extra mile and I will gladly give them my money.

Wonderful as always! My bf and I have been coming here for years, it's such a solid spot for great drinks and delicious light plates. Seasonal drink menu is always on point. Outdoor space was beautiful tonight, comfortably distanced and beautifully lit. Excellent service. Will be back yet again

Drinks were nice, but in general the bar is out of touch with the neighb vibe serving $26 anchovies, $6 bag of chips, and $13 "meat pies". We all want to tip and support bars during COVID, but come on... The meat pie was mostly frozen and inedible. Almost an "f u" to customers as they begrudgingly serve it.
Love the vibe and drinks and music that is just loud enough to set a mood but not ruin a conversation.  Room enough to have a private moment or meet a new friend.  Friendly staff and good energy.

Love the layout great for social gatherings etc. Has a pool table, drinks are not overpriced from what i remember. Staff are cool and dont ID you if you are with someone else they know or who is older. Was 17 when i was there and had no problems being served.
The bar-maid made me feel welcome, but rhen

This is a great neighborhood cocktail bar, especially for those that love whiskey. They serve really good lite bites. The cocktails are pretty good, and are usually liquor forward (meaning quite strong). We’ve been here a handful of times and it’s never super busy, which is nice. It’s also quite large relative to most other NYC bars. Definitely worth a visit if in the neighborhood.
Sweet little cocktail joint. I dont always want a cocktail, but when I do, it's at the Richardson. Nice outdoor area on the street to people watch while I sip my beverage too. Highly recommended.

I just dont! Big boy is the manager and he threw lime in my eye during the storm. Accidents happened. I’m believing. But My fingers n eyes hurt. Fancy treats and then smell that you can’t forget. Picture frames are not even crooked n ghosts don’t seem to hunt. 3/10 out of 5 flying super stars because accidents can happen. Maybe.

Not only a great bar, great for events as well. We had our wedding here and had a blast! All our guests were amazed by the atmosphere, the food and the hospitality. It's also a great bar to go with great cocktails and tasty food selection. Very friendly service as well.

Really stellar food (we shared cheese and charcuterie, fall squash, curried lamb pie, meatballs). Great, friendly service. Perfect ambiance for a delicious casual meal. Cocktails are on point as well. Recommend.
Great space and terrific bartenders!

The unique ambiance leaves you spellbound and you love to visit the place again and again. The place offers so much of fun and frolic.
Some of the best octopus and meatballs I've ever had, paired with fantastic service. Definitely stop here if you're in the neighborhood.
my favorite neighborhood spot. nice cocktails, great staff, yummy snacks. all in all, 👌
Our favorite neighborhood cocktail bar. Well made drinks with a menu that changes periodically. Nice outdoor seating space.

Insanely great gin martinis, fantastic appetizers and great bartenders. Looking forward to the next round soon!

Step back in time when you step foot in here. One of my favorite bars in that neighborhood.  Cocktail game is on point!
Throwback looking bar.  Nice selection of premium alcohol. Good music.  Very dark. Large bar area and a few booth seats. Very laid back and relaxed.
What a local bar ought to be. Never too crowded or too empty, good happy hour, good music, and good snacks. And orange wine! (Would love to have that in the happy hour)

If I could give it no starts I would, I can’t even say if the food or drinks were good or bad because we didn’t even get served. The only thing I got was water and a 30 minute wait. Mind you the bar was not even full and it was a week night. Will never go back to this place.
One of my favorite bars in the city. Great ambiance and music with a rotating menu of creative and strong cocktails.
Great cocktails, great bartenders, this is where you want to have a good drink!

(Translated by Google) Good bar for a beer, peck something or dine in the east part of Williamsburg. They have a terrace that is always full in summer, but the interior is also cozy. The waiters are friendly and in the afternoon they have happy hour. To eat, there are dishes and some sandwiches.  (Original) Buen bar para tomar una cerveza, picotear algo o cenar en la parte este de Williamsburg. Tienen una terraza que en verano siempre está llena, pero el interior también es acogedor. Los camareros son amables y por la tarde tienen happy hour. Para comer, hay platillos y algunos sándwiches.
Real classy feel to this place. Mad friendly bartenders too. A little pricy but eh whaddayagonnado.

Low-key bar with minimal decor, great music, and friendly bartenders. Their menu seems to be constantly changing so things never get boring. This is one of my favorite local spots.

I really enjoy coming here usually for an occasion like birthdays. The staff is really easy going and helpful. The bar gets crowded on the weekends but fortunately they had a few servers taking orders walking around which made the experience really enjoyable.

A group of five of us stopped in here a few weeks ago, intending only to get a few drinks and maybe a snack, and ended up staying for several hours, enjoying the company of the friendly bartender and sampling the goods on the menu.  They have an excellent whiskey selection, and minimal, yet impressive, decor.  I will definitely be back next time I'm in Brooklyn.
This is the best bar of all times. For realz.

Had two friends' birthday in the backroom. it has enough space to host at least 20 people and dim lights, booths will create a chill atmosphere to hang out. the waiters were very nice and understanding

I attended a party here in the private room. It's a good location to host a party since there is a lot of room and the service is great. Instead of going to the bar, the waitress would bring us beers. This feels like somebody's living room. We had a few plates of appetizers like antipasti. It was okay. I left still hungry but had a great time catching up with old friends.

Sigh. I wish I liked this place more. It's reasonably attractive, the people are nice, and the drinks are good. But there are just too many faults. The drinks are overpriced for the neighborhood ($12). The quality of the meat and cheese platter is excellent, but $5 for two little slices of prosciutto is crazy. I liked the outdoor patio, but sitting outdoors with no waitress service just makes the prices even more out of whack.
This bar is so unique and that's why I like it. All the bartenders are men who dress like they are in the 40's. It's cute. The food is cool too.
The bartenders look young for the old-timey feel they're going for, but they're nice.

It's a beautiful bar with a nice cocktail selection. But there are two problems. 1. They play their music SO loud. Even when there are only a few in the bar and it's a late night lounge vibe.. they play silly soundtracks on full blast. 2. AC is always cranked. They keep it lie -2 F. Come with a parka
